title: For Sale:  Magnum Research Deseart Eagle .44 Magnum  -- Satin Nickel
postcontent:
Like new, just gorgeous, stunningly-accurate .44 Magnum in beautiful Satin Nickel finish.  Shot 30-40 times for barrel break-in (cleaning after each of first 12 shots, then after each group of three for 18 more shots) and accuracy testing.  Aside from my Sig P220 Sport .45 ACP, this is the most accurate handgun I've ever shot.  Cared for like a baby, never exposed to bad elements, cleaned meticulously after its few uses.

One major appeal of this pistol is its rapid return to target due to surprisingly manageable recoil.  The gas cycling system aborbs a great deal of the energy, giving this much less muzzle jump than a .44 Mag revolver (I have a Super Blackhawk, and it's a jumper!).  Also, the octagonal rifling lives up to its reputation for accuracy.  This gun will shoot where you point it to a very precise degree.

Selling because I just don't shoot pistols that much anymore and I want her to be in good hands and being used versus sitting in my safe.  Comes with one magazine.  If you are interested, I have Dillon dies for bench loading.
